CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)</t><stat>insert into car (id, brand, model) values (1, 'toyota', 'corolla')</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE engine(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), hp INT)

CREATE TABLE engine(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), hp INT)

CREATE TABLE car(id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand VARCHAR(50), model VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)

CREATE TABLE chassis(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), material VARCHAR(50), color VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))</t><stat>INSERT INTO engine (id, car_id, type, hp) SELECT 1, car.id, 'Electric', 200 FROM car WHERE car.id = 1</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE engine(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), hp INT)

CREATE TABLE car(id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand VARCHAR(50), model VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE chassis(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), material VARCHAR(50), color VARCHAR(50))</t><stat>insert into engine (id, car_id, type, hp) select 1, car.id, 'electric', 200 from car where car.id = 1</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)

CREATE TABLE chassis(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), material VARCHAR(50), color VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)

CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))</t><stat>insert into chassis (id, car_id, material, color) select 1, car.id, 'carbon fiber', 'black' from car where car.id = 1</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE engine(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), hp INT)

CREATE TABLE car(id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand VARCHAR(50), model VARCHAR(50))</t><stat>INSERT INTO chassis (id, car_id, material, color) SELECT 1, car.id, 'Carbon Fiber', 'Black' FROM car WHERE car.id = 1</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE engine(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), hp INT)

CREATE TABLE car(id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand VARCHAR(50), model VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE chassis(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), material VARCHAR(50), color VARCHAR(50))</t><stat>insert into chassis (id, car_id, material, color) select 1, car.id, 'carbon fiber', 'black' from car where car.id = 1</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)

CREATE TABLE chassis(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), material VARCHAR(50), color VARCHAR(50))</t><stat>INSERT INTO tire (id, car_id, brand, size, type) SELECT 1, car.id, 'Michelin', '17', 'Summer' FROM car WHERE car.id = 1</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE car(id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand VARCHAR(50), model VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE car(id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand VARCHAR(50), model VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE engine(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), hp INT)

CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)</t><stat>INSERT INTO tire (id, car_id, brand, size, type) SELECT 1, car.id, 'Michelin', '17', 'Summer' FROM car WHERE car.id = 1</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE chassis(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), material VARCHAR(50), color VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE car(id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand VARCHAR(50), model VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)

CREATE TABLE chassis(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), material VARCHAR(50), color VARCHAR(50))</t><stat>INSERT INTO tire (id, car_id, brand, size, type) SELECT 1, car.id, 'Michelin', '17', 'Summer' FROM car WHERE car.id = 1</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))</t><stat>INSERT INTO tire (id, car_id, brand, size, type) SELECT 1, car.id, 'Michelin', '17', 'Summer' FROM car WHERE car.id = 1</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)

CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)</t><stat>INSERT INTO maintenance (id, car_id, type, date) SELECT 1, car.id, 'Oil Change', '2022-01-05' FROM car WHERE car.id = 1</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE chassis(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), material VARCHAR(50), color VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE car(id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand VARCHAR(50), model VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)

CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))</t><stat>INSERT INTO engine (id, car_id, type, hp) SELECT 2, car.id, 'Gasoline', 150 FROM car WHERE car.id = 2</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE chassis(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), material VARCHAR(50), color VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)</t><stat>insert into engine (id, car_id, type, hp) select 2, car.id, 'gasoline', 150 from car where car.id = 2</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE car(id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand VARCHAR(50), model VARCHAR(50))</t><stat>insert into engine (id, car_id, type, hp) select 2, car.id, 'gasoline', 150 from car where car.id = 2</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)

CREATE TABLE car(id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand VARCHAR(50), model VARCHAR(50))</t><stat>insert into chassis (id, car_id, material, color) select 2, car.id, 'steel', 'red' from car where car.id = 2</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE engine(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), hp INT)</t><stat>INSERT INTO chassis (id, car_id, material, color) SELECT 2, car.id, 'Steel', 'Red' FROM car WHERE car.id = 2</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)

CREATE TABLE car(id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand VARCHAR(50), model VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)

CREATE TABLE chassis(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), material VARCHAR(50), color VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))</t><stat>insert into tire (id, car_id, brand, size, type) select 2, car.id, 'bridgestone', '16', 'all-season' from car where car.id = 2</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE engine(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), hp INT)

CREATE TABLE car(id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand VARCHAR(50), model VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE engine(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), hp INT)

CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))</t><stat>INSERT INTO tire (id, car_id, brand, size, type) SELECT 2, car.id, 'Bridgestone', '16', 'All-Season' FROM car WHERE car.id = 2</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE chassis(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), material VARCHAR(50), color VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)

CREATE TABLE car(id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand VARCHAR(50), model VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE chassis(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), material VARCHAR(50), color VARCHAR(50))</t><stat>insert into tire (id, car_id, brand, size, type) select 2, car.id, 'bridgestone', '16', 'all-season' from car where car.id = 2</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)

CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE car(id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand VARCHAR(50), model VARCHAR(50))</t><stat>INSERT INTO maintenance (id, car_id, type, date) SELECT 2, car.id, 'Tire Rotation', '2022-02-15' FROM car WHERE car.id = 2</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE chassis(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), material VARCHAR(50), color VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE car(id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand VARCHAR(50), model VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE chassis(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), material VARCHAR(50), color VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)</t><stat>INSERT INTO maintenance (id, car_id, type, date) SELECT 2, car.id, 'Tire Rotation', '2022-02-15' FROM car WHERE car.id = 2</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE engine(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), hp INT)

CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE chassis(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), material VARCHAR(50), color VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)

CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))</t><stat>insert into engine (id, car_id, type, hp) select 3, car.id, 'petrol', 300 from car where car.id = 3</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE car(id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand VARCHAR(50), model VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE car(id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand VARCHAR(50), model VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)

CREATE TABLE chassis(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), material VARCHAR(50), color VARCHAR(50))</t><stat>insert into chassis (id, car_id, material, color) select 3, car.id, 'aluminum', 'blue' from car where car.id = 3</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE engine(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), hp INT)

CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE car(id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand VARCHAR(50), model VARCHAR(50))</t><stat>INSERT INTO chassis (id, car_id, material, color) SELECT 3, car.id, 'Aluminum', 'Blue' FROM car WHERE car.id = 3</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE chassis(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), material VARCHAR(50), color VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE chassis(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), material VARCHAR(50), color VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))</t><stat>INSERT INTO chassis (id, car_id, material, color) SELECT 3, car.id, 'Aluminum', 'Blue' FROM car WHERE car.id = 3</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)

CREATE TABLE chassis(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), material VARCHAR(50), color VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE engine(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), hp INT)</t><stat>insert into chassis (id, car_id, material, color) select 3, car.id, 'aluminum', 'blue' from car where car.id = 3</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)

CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE car(id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand VARCHAR(50), model VARCHAR(50))</t><stat>insert into tire (id, car_id, brand, size, type) select 3, car.id, 'goodyear', '18', 'performance' from car where car.id = 3</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE engine(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), hp INT)

CREATE TABLE chassis(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), material VARCHAR(50), color VARCHAR(50))</t><stat>insert into tire (id, car_id, brand, size, type) select 3, car.id, 'goodyear', '18', 'performance' from car where car.id = 3</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE engine(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), hp INT)</t><stat>insert into tire (id, car_id, brand, size, type) select 3, car.id, 'goodyear', '18', 'performance' from car where car.id = 3</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)

CREATE TABLE car(id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand VARCHAR(50), model VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)

CREATE TABLE chassis(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), material VARCHAR(50), color VARCHAR(50))</t><stat>insert into maintenance (id, car_id, type, date) select 3, car.id, 'brake pad replacement', '2022-03-25' from car where car.id = 3</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE engine(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), hp INT)

CREATE TABLE engine(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), hp INT)

CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)</t><stat>INSERT INTO maintenance (id, car_id, type, date) SELECT 3, car.id, 'Brake Pad Replacement', '2022-03-25' FROM car WHERE car.id = 3</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE car(id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand VARCHAR(50), model VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE chassis(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), material VARCHAR(50), color VARCHAR(50))</t><stat>INSERT INTO maintenance (id, car_id, type, date) SELECT 3, car.id, 'Brake Pad Replacement', '2022-03-25' FROM car WHERE car.id = 3</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)

CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))</t><stat>insert into car (id, brand, model) values (4, 'chevrolet', 'camaro')</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE car(id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand VARCHAR(50), model VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))</t><stat>insert into engine (id, car_id, type, hp) select 4, car.id, 'diesel', 250 from car where car.id = 4</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE car(id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand VARCHAR(50), model VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE car(id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand VARCHAR(50), model VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)

CREATE TABLE car(id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand VARCHAR(50), model VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE engine(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), hp INT)

CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))</t><stat>INSERT INTO engine (id, car_id, type, hp) SELECT 4, car.id, 'Diesel', 250 FROM car WHERE car.id = 4</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE chassis(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), material VARCHAR(50), color VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)

CREATE TABLE car(id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand VARCHAR(50), model VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)

CREATE TABLE engine(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), hp INT)</t><stat>insert into engine (id, car_id, type, hp) select 4, car.id, 'diesel', 250 from car where car.id = 4</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE car(id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand VARCHAR(50), model VARCHAR(50))</t><stat>INSERT INTO engine (id, car_id, type, hp) SELECT 4, car.id, 'Diesel', 250 FROM car WHERE car.id = 4</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)

CREATE TABLE car(id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand VARCHAR(50), model VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE chassis(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), material VARCHAR(50), color VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)</t><stat>INSERT INTO chassis (id, car_id, material, color) SELECT 4, car.id, 'Fiberglass', 'Yellow' FROM car WHERE car.id = 4</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE engine(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), hp INT)

CREATE TABLE car(id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand VARCHAR(50), model VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE chassis(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), material VARCHAR(50), color VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE engine(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), hp INT)</t><stat>insert into chassis (id, car_id, material, color) select 4, car.id, 'fiberglass', 'yellow' from car where car.id = 4</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)

CREATE TABLE chassis(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), material VARCHAR(50), color VARCHAR(50))</t><stat>insert into tire (id, car_id, brand, size, type) select 4, car.id, 'pirelli', '19', 'high-performance' from car where car.id = 4</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE car(id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand VARCHAR(50), model VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE car(id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand VARCHAR(50), model VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)</t><stat>insert into tire (id, car_id, brand, size, type) select 4, car.id, 'pirelli', '19', 'high-performance' from car where car.id = 4</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE engine(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), hp INT)

CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)</t><stat>insert into maintenance (id, car_id, type, date) select 4, car.id, 'engine tune-up', '2022-04-10' from car where car.id = 4</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE car(id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand VARCHAR(50), model VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE car(id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand VARCHAR(50), model VARCHAR(50))

CREATE TABLE maintenance(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)

CREATE TABLE tire(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), brand VARCHAR(50), size VARCHAR(10), type VARCHAR(50))</t><stat>insert into maintenance (id, car_id, type, date) select 4, car.id, 'engine tune-up', '2022-04-10' from car where car.id = 4</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE engine(id INT PRIMARY KEY, car_id INT REFERENCES car(id), type VARCHAR(50), hp INT)
